/ghonmv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ghonmv/future_shock"},{"short_id":"gozgx2","created_at":"2026-03-04T05:58:25.000-06:00","title":"Slopful Things","url":"https://kyefox.com/slopful-things/","score":1,"flags":3,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Kye","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gozgx2","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gozgx2/slopful_things"},{"short_id":"rqvdts","created_at":"2026-03-04T05:32:11.000-06:00","title":"Agentic Engineering Patterns","url":"https://simonwillison.net/guides/agentic-engineering-patterns/","score":2,"flags":2,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"mpweiher","user_is_author":false,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rqvdts","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rqvdts/agentic_engineering_patterns"},{"short_id":"dc3ysd","created_at":"2026-03-04T05:11:02.000-06:00","title":"Package Managers Need to Cool Down","url":"https://nesbitt.io/2026/03/04/package-managers-need-to-cool-down.html","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"JamieTanna","user_is_author":false,"tags":["practices"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dc3ysd","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dc3ysd/package_managers_need_cool_down"},{"short_id":"oh8r3r","created_at":"2026-03-04T05:00:05.000-06:00","title":"Object-Oriented Programming: Themes and Variations (1985)","url":"https://ojs.aaai.org/aimagazine/index.php/aimagazine/article/download/508/444","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"amoroso","user_is_author":false,"tags":["historical","lisp","pdf"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oh8r3r","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oh8r3r/object_oriented_programming_themes"},{"short_id":"oi2emm","created_at":"2026-03-04T04:15:36.000-06:00","title":"pg_jitter: Better JIT for Postgres","url":"https://github.com/vladich/pg_jitter","score":10,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"fanf","user_is_author":false,"tags":["compilers","databases"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oi2emm","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oi2emm/pg_jitter_better_jit_for_postgres"},{"short_id":"2ng9uk","created_at":"2026-03-04T02:54:08.000-06:00","title":"RTL: WTF: Read the web like Right-to-Left readers do","url":"https://rtl.wtf/","score":15,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"kana","user_is_author":false,"tags":["a11y","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2ng9uk","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2ng9uk/rtl_wtf_read_web_like_right_left_readers_do"},{"short_id":"ya5b5h","created_at":"2026-03-04T02:24:51.000-06:00","title":"Proposal: Add `Guix` tag","url":"","score":20,"flags":0,"comment_count":17,"description":"\u003cp\u003eIt is viewed as just a nix fork with scheme on top of in many communities I am in, while yes it might be started off as that but it has grown significantly in the recent years that it should be treated as its own project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have been just in guix community for like year and so but I have seen very good changes, some of them would\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe new rust build system\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMoving to Codeberg (this brought many new contributors)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003enew v1.5.0 release :)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut what I like most about the guix project is the people there, It is small but very tightly-knit community. So I believe guix deserve its own tag now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eps - I am adding more text that follows the guidelines, thanks \u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/~gerikson\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003e@gerikson\u003c/a\u003e for pointing this out\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eName: \"guix\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDescription: \"A transactional scheme based package manager and distribution\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCategory: package management, declarative configuration\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSimilar tag: nix\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRecent Stories:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/98geyn/64_bit_hurd_has_landed_guix\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/98geyn/64_bit_hurd_has_landed_guix\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/oysfmo/debugging_reproducibility_issues_rust\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/oysfmo/debugging_reproducibility_issues_rust\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/6audzp/hacklog_diffing_comparing_guix\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/6audzp/hacklog_diffing_comparing_guix\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/4zmz17/setting_up_cuirass_locally\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/4zmz17/setting_up_cuirass_locally\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/ytqpkb/how_i_manage_my_guix_system_configs\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/ytqpkb/how_i_manage_my_guix_system_configs\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/uysha5/adventures_guix_packaging\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/uysha5/adventures_guix_packaging\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/koagyg/guix_system_first_impressions_as_nix_user\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/koagyg/guix_system_first_impressions_as_nix_user\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/zhsi80/gnu_guix_1_5_0_released\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/zhsi80/gnu_guix_1_5_0_released\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePeople who use nix might want to filter out guix stories that have got nothing to do with it and vice-versa for guix people.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe increased complexity for submitter and mods is justified by the fact that this tag will set a clear distinction between the two and this should make it easy for both submitter and mods as tagging \u003ccode\u003egnu guix 1.5.0\u003c/code\u003e release as nix tag doesn't seem right.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"It is viewed as just a nix fork with scheme on top of in many communities I am in, while yes it might be started off as that but it has grown significantly in the recent years that it should be treated as its own project.\r\n\r\nI have been just in guix community for like year and so but I have seen very good changes, some of them would\r\n\r\n- The new rust build system\r\n- Moving to Codeberg (this brought many new contributors)\r\n- new v1.5.0 release :)\r\n\r\nBut what I like most about the guix project is the people there, It is small but very tightly-knit community. So I believe guix deserve its own tag now.\r\n\r\nps - I am adding more text that follows the guidelines, thanks @gerikson for pointing this out\r\n\r\n----------\r\n\r\nName: \"guix\"\r\n\r\nDescription: \"A transactional scheme based package manager and distribution\"\r\n\r\nCategory: package management, declarative configuration\r\n\r\nSimilar tag: nix\r\n\r\nRecent Stories:\r\n\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/98geyn/64_bit_hurd_has_landed_guix\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/oysfmo/debugging_reproducibility_issues_rust\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/6audzp/hacklog_diffing_comparing_guix\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/4zmz17/setting_up_cuirass_locally\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/ytqpkb/how_i_manage_my_guix_system_configs\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/uysha5/adventures_guix_packaging\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/koagyg/guix_system_first_impressions_as_nix_user\r\n- https://lobste.rs/s/zhsi80/gnu_guix_1_5_0_released\r\n\r\nPeople who use nix might want to filter out guix stories that have got nothing to do with it and vice-versa for guix people.\r\n\r\nThe increased complexity for submitter and mods is justified by the fact that this tag will set a clear distinction between the two and this should make it easy for both submitter and mods as tagging `gnu guix 1.5.0` release as nix tag doesn't seem right.","submitter_user":"untrusem","user_is_author":true,"tags":["meta"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ya5b5h","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ya5b5h/proposal_add_guix_tag"},{"short_id":"ftnuxf","created_at":"2026-03-03T22:19:56.000-06:00","title":"Coruna: The Mysterious Journey of a Powerful iOS Exploit Kit","url":"https://cloud.google.com/blog/topics/threat-intelligence/coruna-powerful-ios-exploit-kit","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"vaguelytagged","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ios","security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ftnuxf","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ftnuxf/coruna_mysterious_journey_powerful_ios"},{"short_id":"isuqoa","created_at":"2026-03-03T21:49:04.000-06:00","title":"Never snooze a future","url":"https://jacko.io/snooze.html","score":25,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"thunderseethe","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/isuqoa","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/isuqoa/never_snooze_future"},{"short_id":"hz6vhv","created_at":"2026-03-03T21:32:02.000-06:00","title":"California's Digital Age Assurance Act, and FOSS","url":"https://runxiyu.org/comp/ab1043/","score":14,"flags":0,"comment_count":12,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"runxiyu","user_is_author":true,"tags":["law","privacy"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hz6vhv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hz6vhv/california_s_digital_age_assurance_act"},{"short_id":"hu6tos","created_at":"2026-03-03T17:29:32.000-06:00","title":"The Markless Document Markup Standard","url":"https://shirakumo.org/docs/markless/","score":17,"flags":0,"comment_count":13,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchon